# Thought Flow Project Notes

Thought Flow is a Tauri + React + Vite desktop app for generating and viewing
flowcharts from chat prompts.

## Runtime Flow

1. Files live in the user's documents directory under `thought-flow`.
2. Opening a file creates a tab via `src/store/tabStore.ts`.
3. Each file stores JSON chat messages, then `\n[+]\n`, then a JSON chart.
4. `src/components/ChatPanel.tsx` sends chat history to the configured LLM.
5. The LLM is instructed to return Mermaid flowchart syntax.
6. Mermaid text is parsed into `ChartGraph`.
7. The active renderer displays that graph.
8. The tab is saved back to disk through Tauri FS APIs.

## Important Files

- `src/App.tsx`: app shell, renderer toggle, layout composition.
- `src/components/ChatPanel.tsx`: chat UI and LLM streaming pipeline.
- `src/lib/llm.ts`: Ollama, OpenAI-compatible, and Anthropic streaming clients.
- `src/lib/chart/types.ts`: central `ChartGraph` data model.
- `src/lib/chart/mermaid.ts`: Mermaid parse/serialize helpers.
- `src/lib/chart/streamParse.ts`: tolerant partial parser for live preview.
- `src/lib/chart/validate.ts`: structural cleanup after final parse.
- `src/components/MermaidRenderer.tsx`: Mermaid.js renderer.
- `src/components/Flowchart/index.tsx`: custom SVG renderer.
- `src/components/Flowchart/layout.ts`: Dagre layout.
- `src/components/sidebar/*`: file explorer, context menu, drag/drop.
- `src/store/settingsStore.ts`: theme and LLM settings.
- `src/store/tabStore.ts`: tabs, messages, chart load/save.
- `src/store/layoutStore.ts`: persisted sidebar/chat layout state.

## Chart Pipeline

The internal graph type is `ChartGraph`.

Mermaid comes in through either:

- `parseStreamingChart(...)` during live preview.
- `mermaidToChart(...)` after the full response finishes.

After final parsing, `validateAndFix(...)` removes broken/duplicate edges and
ensures start/end nodes exist when possible.

## Renderers

The app has two renderer modes:

- `mermaid`: converts `ChartGraph` back to Mermaid and renders with Mermaid.js.
- `custom`: lays out the graph with Dagre and draws SVG nodes/edges directly.

Both support pan, zoom, fit-to-view, and keyboard-style node playback.

## Notes / Gotchas

- `chartToMermaid(...)` emits a custom `title:` line. Mermaid.js rejects that
  line, so `MermaidRenderer` strips it before rendering.
- `streamLLM(...)` supports a `currentChart` argument for patch/edit mode, but
  `ChatPanel` currently calls it without passing the active chart.
- The repo currently has local uncommitted changes. Do not revert unrelated
  edits unless explicitly asked.
